FAIR data

Not just for your own mental health, but also because of agreements for EU projects

H2020 Programme Guidelines

Metadata

Sharing data only is not enough. You need data about the data.

image credit: I got this slide from Ted Laderas

Examples metadata:

  • date experiment was done
  • time of measurements
  • who did the data collection
  • who paid for the research
  • experimental design
  • etc etc

Types of meta data

According to How to FAIR :

  • Administrative metadata: relevant for managing; E.g. principal investigator, project collaborators, funder, project period, etc.
  • Descriptive or citation metadata: relevant for linking data to communications E.g. authors, title, abstract, keywords
  • Structural metadata: experimental design and data structure E.g. collection method, sample size, categories, variables
